Camden.Spring Garden station (Market\u2013Frank: The Market–Frankford Line (MFL) (also called the Market–Frankford Subway–Elevated Line (MFSE), the Market-Frankford El (MFE), the El (), or the Blue Line) is a rapid transit line in Philadelphia, operated by SEPTA. It runs from the 69th Street Transportation Center in Upper Darby, just outside of West Philadelphia, to the Frankford Transportation Center in Near Northeast Philadelphia. With more than 187,000 boardings on an average weekday, it is the busiest route in the SEPTA system. Although it is an elevated train, it does run underground beneath Market Street for part of the route.
